title:
ParkUsher
1.0.03

creator: SoenLabs
descriptionHtml:
AS SEEN ON CITYNEWS MONTREAL. Scans are free forever!

1. Scan any Montreal parking sign (Free and unlimited...forever)
2. Know if you can park or not
3. Enjoy Montreal with confidence 🚗
4. Get a reminder when you need to move your car

And here's the cool part: Never worry about staying too long in a parking spot again! With ParkUsher's timer feature, you won't have to rush back to your car (and risk slipping on ice).

Our founders are working tirelessly, fueled by poutine and maple syrup, to unleash more features that will make downtown Montreal your playground.

The scans are and always will be free.

💚 But here’s what’s in it for you if you decide to support us:

- Locate your parked car with a reminder map.
- Maintain a record of your past parking locations for potential ticket disputes.
- Add unlimited vehicles to your ParkUsher account.

title:
ParkUsher Montreal Parking App
1.0.11

creator: SoenLabs
descriptionHtml:
Available Now in Montreal & New York!
(More cities coming soon)
Say goodbye to parking stress with ParkUsher, your ultimate guide to hassle-free parking. Whether you’re navigating Montreal’s Mount Royal, seeking parking near Trudeau Airport, or tackling the busy streets of New York City, ParkUsher ensures you find the best spots quickly and confidently.

Key Features:

* Free Unlimited Parking Sign Scans: Decode complex parking rules instantly.
* Real-Time Street Parking Map (Free): Easily locate legal spots with green lines for allowed parking and red lines for no-parking zones.
* Parking Timer & Alerts: Never overstay your welcome with timely notifications.
* Plan Your Parking Day: Perfect for Mount Royal Montreal parking, Trudeau Airport parking, and busy city streets.

Introducing ParkUsher Pro
Previously paid users are upgraded to ParkUsher Pro, unlocking even more features:

* Blue lines = Paid street parking
* Filter between paid and free parking
* See parking options in advance

How ParkUsher Works

1. Scan Any Parking Sign
Confused by parking signs? Just point your camera at any parking sign in Montreal or New York, and ParkUsher’s AI will interpret the rules for you in seconds. Parking scans are free forever—no subscriptions, no limits.
2. Real-Time Street Parking Map (Free)
Finding parking just got easier with the free real-time map! Green lines show legal parking, while red lines indicate no-parking zones. No more circling the block—ParkUsher guides you to available spots.
3. Parking Timer & Notifications
Stay stress-free with our timer feature. Set a timer once you park, and ParkUsher will alert you before your time is up to help you avoid fines.
4. Plan Your Parking Day
Whether you’re running errands, exploring Mount Royal, or catching a flight from Trudeau Airport, ParkUsher makes it easy to plan ahead and navigate Montreal and NYC with confidence.

Why Choose ParkUsher?

* Free & Easy to Use: Parking sign scanning is always free.
* Accurate AI Assistance: Our AI quickly decodes parking signs, saving you time.
* Save Time & Money: Avoid tickets and save on parking costs with smart planning.
* ParkUsher Pro: Upgrade to Pro to unlock paid parking features like filtering between paid/free spaces and seeing parking availability ahead of time.

How to Get Started

* Is the app really free?
Yes! The parking sign scanner is completely free forever. The real-time street parking map is now free for all users.
* What cities are supported?
Currently, ParkUsher supports Montreal and New York, with more cities coming soon!
* How does the parking map work?
The map shows live data of legal parking areas with green lines for allowed parking and red lines for restricted zones. For ParkUsher Pro users, blue lines show paid parking spots.
* How do I set a parking timer?
Tap the timer icon once parked, set your duration, and ParkUsher will notify you when time’s up!

Stop wasting time and start parking smarter. Get ParkUsher today to simplify parking in Montreal and New York. More cities coming soon!

Terms and Conditions: https://www.parkusher.app/legal/terms-conditions

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
This update includes exactly 37.2% more stability (or is it less? It’s hard to tell). We also fixed 92% of the bugs, though the remaining 8% are currently on vacation.

The timer’s now 3.6% more precise, but don’t ask us how we calculated that. There’s also a feature that makes things slightly faster, unless you’re standing still—then it’s just regular speed.

It’s all better, or maybe it’s not. But hey, it’s an update.
